\chapter{Desserts}

\subsection*{CHOCOLATE LAVA CAKE} \index{Gluten Free!cake} \index{CHOCOLATE LAVA CAKE} \index{cake!Gluten Free} \index{cake!Low Carb} \index{Low Carb!cake}
		\begin{multicols}{2}
			\begin{itemize}[\tightlists]
				\item 5 Tbsp salted butter
				\item	1 cup chocolate chips
				\item 2 Tbsp almond flour	
				\item 1 Tbsp (heaping) cocoa powder
				\item	1/8 tsp sea salt	
				\item 2 large eggs
				\item	2 large egg yolks	
				\item 3 Tbsp sugar
				\item 1/4 tsp vanilla extract	
			\end{itemize}
		\end{multicols}
Melt butter and chocolate chips in a double boiler. Combine almond flour, cocoa powder, and salt in a small mixing bowl. In a large mixing bowl whisk eggs, sugar, and vanilla. Fold in chocolate. Sift in dry ingredients. Butter four 4-oz ramekins and fill with chocolate mixture. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Place ramekins in hot water bath and bake at 425$^\circ$F for 15-18 minutes. Let cool for 10 minutes.


